snippet.textDisplay: So using a toner won’t lighten your hair, toner adjusts the unwanted tones in your hair, purple takes out yellow tones and blue will take out orangey unwanted tones in your hair. Your roots are orange because your scalp is a heat zone and will process a lot faster. You would either have to lighten the roots again or do a root smudge with a darker color😉❤️
snippet.textOriginal: So using a toner won’t lighten your hair, toner adjusts the unwanted tones in your hair, purple takes out yellow tones and blue will take out orangey unwanted tones in your hair. snippet.textDisplay:
You look so good in blonde Work It Girl 😍

& I would definitely recommend using a comb while I using bleach & Developer just so it could blend good & so you don’t miss any part. If you were to bleach the roots again use a 10 or 20 developer so it’s not as damaging. & don’t use the purple shampoo too often because it could dry out your hair when I had my hair blonde for 2 yrs I would just use it about once or twice a week. But when you do use it let the shampoo or conditioner sit on your hair for about 10 mins when I would do that it would leave my hair line a slight lavender/grayish blonde

snippet.textDisplay: Okay so first of all Sarah you did an amazing job! Second of all I am a hair dresser and your roots are an easy fix. You can do a root drop, I would use like a level 7. You might want to get someone to help you because it's kinda hard to do your own roots especially in the back. You want to apply it about an inch or 2 down. You can look up videos on how to color roots if you're not sure how to do it, it's super easy.  Once you are done applying comb it through with a comb not a brush. Dont worry too much about blending when you are applying it because when you comb it through thatll get rid of harsh lines. Also the reason the toner didnt work was because you needed a blue based toner instead of a purple based kinda like why your hair was still brassy after the first video because your hair was not light enough for the purple toner. So If you still want to stay blonde at the roots you can either bleach again and use same toner or just buy a blue based one 😊 hope this helped!
